---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Sponsor"
  description="Support Nikky Amresh's open-source work, technical writing, and developer tooling via GitHub Sponsors."
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-prose px-4 pb-20 pt-12 sm:px-6 sm:pt-16 lg:px-8">
    <header>
      <p class="font-mono text-2xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-accent">Sponsor</p>
      <h1 class="mt-2 text-3xl font-medium tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
        Support the work.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
        I write backend systems, ship developer tooling, publish open-source
        projects, and write long-form technical notes. If any of that has helped
        you or your team, you can sponsor the work through GitHub Sponsors.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="prose prose-invert mt-12">
      <h2>What you&rsquo;re sponsoring</h2>
      <p>
        Sponsorship supports ongoing effort on the following — all free and
        publicly available at no cost to anyone:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Open-source libraries and VS Code extensions</strong> —
          maintenance, releases, documentation, and issue triage.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Technical writing</strong> — long-form posts on backend
          architecture, platform engineering, and developer tooling.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>CTF challenges and security research</strong> — challenge
          design, writeups, and tooling published to the community.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Answering questions and reviewing code</strong> for sponsors
          who want occasional input (tier-dependent).
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Tiers</h2>
      <p>
        Sponsorship is processed through GitHub Sponsors. Tiers are one-time or
        recurring (monthly). You can cancel a recurring sponsorship at any time
        from your GitHub billing settings; billing stops at the end of the
        current cycle.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Supporter</strong> — a thank-you. Name listed on a public
          sponsors page if you opt in.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Backer</strong> — everything above, plus early access to
          drafts of long-form posts before they go public.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Patron</strong> — everything above, plus a short monthly
          email with what I&rsquo;m working on and occasional Q&amp;A.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What sponsorship isn&rsquo;t</h2>
      <p>
        Sponsorship is a voluntary contribution to ongoing open-source and
        writing work. It is not a contract for deliverables, not a consulting
        engagement, and not a service-level commitment. If you need dedicated
        work for your team, please reach out directly &mdash; sponsorship is
        not the right channel for that.
      </p>

      <h2>Payments and billing</h2>
      <p>
        All payments are processed by GitHub and their payment processor
        (Stripe). I do not store, handle, or have access to your payment-card
        information. Refund and cancellation terms are described on the
        <a href="/refunds">refunds page</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Questions</h2>
      <p>
        Email <a href="mailto:nikkyamresh8@gmail.com">nikkyamresh8@gmail.com</a>
        or see the <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="mt-16">
      <a href="/" class="font-mono text-sm text-accent no-underline hover:underline underline-offset-4">
        ← Back to home
      </a>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
